----------------------------------------------------------------------
-- Whole-model verification summary
----------------------------------------------------------------------

-- Summary 1: Defines a structural and behavioral model for the Inventory Dashboard Display requirement.
-- Summary 2: Model includes actors, resources (StockLevels, ExpirationData, TransfusionRequestData), interfaces, permissions, and a core operation sig.
-- Summary 3: Covers acceptance criteria, edge cases, and test scenarios through predicates and assertions.
-- Summary 4: Non-functional requirements are proxied via invariants on channel/resource counts.
-- Assumption 1: The dashboard operation is modeled as a single sig with pre/post states.
-- Assumption 2: Three concrete resource sigs represent the data sections: StockLevels, ExpirationData, TransfusionRequestData.
-- Assumption 3: Precondition is a single state Pre1 (logged in as blood bank manager).
-- Assumption 4: Non-functional requirements are approximated by constraints on channel and resource numbers.
-- Open issue 1: Edge case assertions (ec_safe_1, ec_safe_2, ec_safe_3) may be trivially satisfied due to lack of detailed expiration modeling.
-- Open issue 2: Conflict between nfr_fact_latency (max 2 channels) and nfr_fact_redundancy (min 2 channels) forces exactly 2 channels per operation.
-- Open issue 3: nfr_fact_concurrent_actors forces both Actor instances to initiate operations, which may over-constrain the model.


